  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n  \r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">RADIOACTIVITY<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Alpha particle, positively charged particle, identical to the nucleus of the helium-4 atom, spontaneously emitted by some radioactive substances, consisting of two protons and two neutrons bound together, thus having a mass of four units and a positive charge of two.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Beta particles are equivalent to an electron; they are emitted by neutron rich unstable nuclei. Beta particles are high energy electrons. These electrons are not electrons from the electron shells around the nucleus, but are generated when a neutron in the nucleus splits to form a proton and an accompanying electron.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A gamma ray, or gamma radiation (symbol &gamma;), is a penetrating electromagnetic radiation arising from the radioactive decay of atomic nuclei. The mass and proton numbers do not change. It consists of the shortest wavelength electromagnetic waves and so imparts the highest photon energy.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A chain reaction refers to a process in which neutrons released in fission produce an additional fission in at least one further nucleus. This nucleus in turn produces neutrons, and the process repeats. The process may be controlled (nuclear power) or uncontrolled (nuclear weapons).<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In fission, heavy metals are being bombarded with neutrons, nuclei with heavy atoms can be divided into several fragments formed by nuclei with lighter atoms, with neutron emission and a large release of energy. This type of nuclear reaction is called &ldquo;nuclear fission reaction&rdquo;.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Fission is the splitting up of the nucleus of a heavy element into two approximate equal parts with the release of a huge amount of energy and neutrons. Fission takes place only if the bombarding neutron is slow. Graphite is used round the uranium to slow down the neutron, so that the chain reaction will continue. Note fission is the splitting up of the nucleus of heavy metal into two approximate equal parts to release huge energy and neutrons.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Fusion is a nuclear process in which two or more light nuclei combine or fuse to form a heavier nucleus with the release of a large amount of energy<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In a nuclear fusion experiment, the loss of m amount to 1.0x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;kg. The amount of energy obtained from the fusion (speed of light = 3.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">m\/s) is<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. 3.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">J, B. 3.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">J, C. 9.0x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-4<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">J, D. 9.0 x10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>10<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;J<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D (2006\/2007, no15)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Energy = mc<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>2<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">m = 1.0x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;kg, c = 3.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">m\/s, E =?<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">E = 1.0x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>-6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;x (3.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>6<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">)<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>2<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">E = 9.0 x 10<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sup>10&nbsp;<\/sup><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">J<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A substance has a half-life of 3min. After 6m the count rate was observed to be 600.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What its count rate at zero time?<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. 200, B. 1200, C. 1600, D. 2400<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D (2006\/2007, no13)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Given that the half-life = 3mins<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">6mins Count rate = 600<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">3mins Count rate = 2 x 600 = 1200<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">0mins count rate = 2 x 1200 = 2400<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">4g of radioactive material of half-life 10days is spilled on a laboratory floor. How long would it take to disintegrate 3.5g of the material?<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. 11\/4 days, B. 8 1\/4 days, C. 30 days, D. 80 days<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2005\/2006 no2)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The amount remaining after the disintegration is given by;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">4g &ndash; 3.5 = 0.5g<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Since the half-life is 10days,&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">After 10days, 4g&nbsp;<\/span><img src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAB4AAAAaCAYAAACgoey0AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAGBSURBVEhL7ZS9isJAFEaDCkIa9RHSi5WVrbUpxFcRCwvBR7CxESsLixQWNr5AAjaKFqKVFqKF4E8lUeZb7nCjKySuqDsLsgcG5n4kOXPJZTT8AUKI\/ueLXdflnUJxp9OBrusklLUSca1Wg23b0DRNrdjjX\/y54mq1ikKhcFm9Xi9YfDqdeHcLndg79Sv4iunDqVQKk8mEkyuNRgOlUomr5wnsuNvtIhqNYjabcQK0Wi0kk8mbG+hZAsWEJ5\/P52g2m4jFYm+REnfFBA1CJBKRE7nf7zl9nGKxKN\/1WffFdN2FQiH58Gq14vR17nZM0nA4jO12i8FgIDt\/lzxQXK\/XZae73Y4TYDQaIR6P43g8cvI8vmIaIMMwcDgcOLliWRbK5TJXj1GpVJBOp5FIJGCapsx+HK530G63eQf569brtRqxx\/l8lr+PUCYmaTabxXK5lLUSMd37+Xwem82GE0XiXC4Hx3GwWCwwHA4xHo9\/XzydTpHJZG4W3f9Kh+s7Qoj+FxqHkZPmFRufAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC\" width=\"30\" height=\"26\" alt=\"\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;= 2g of the material remaining<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">After 20days, 2g&nbsp;<\/span><img src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAB4AAAAaCAYAAACgoey0AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAGBSURBVEhL7ZS9isJAFEaDCkIa9RHSi5WVrbUpxFcRCwvBR7CxESsLixQWNr5AAjaKFqKVFqKF4E8lUeZb7nCjKySuqDsLsgcG5n4kOXPJZTT8AUKI\/ueLXdflnUJxp9OBrusklLUSca1Wg23b0DRNrdjjX\/y54mq1ikKhcFm9Xi9YfDqdeHcLndg79Sv4iunDqVQKk8mEkyuNRgOlUomr5wnsuNvtIhqNYjabcQK0Wi0kk8mbG+hZAsWEJ5\/P52g2m4jFYm+REnfFBA1CJBKRE7nf7zl9nGKxKN\/1WffFdN2FQiH58Gq14vR17nZM0nA4jO12i8FgIDt\/lzxQXK\/XZae73Y4TYDQaIR6P43g8cvI8vmIaIMMwcDgcOLliWRbK5TJXj1GpVJBOp5FIJGCapsx+HK530G63eQf569brtRqxx\/l8lr+PUCYmaTabxXK5lLUSMd37+Xwem82GE0XiXC4Hx3GwWCwwHA4xHo9\/XzydTpHJZG4W3f9Kh+s7Qoj+FxqHkZPmFRufAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC\" width=\"30\" height=\"26\" alt=\"\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;= 1g<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">After 30days, 1g&nbsp;<\/span><img src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAB4AAAAaCAYAAACgoey0AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAGBSURBVEhL7ZS9isJAFEaDCkIa9RHSi5WVrbUpxFcRCwvBR7CxESsLixQWNr5AAjaKFqKVFqKF4E8lUeZb7nCjKySuqDsLsgcG5n4kOXPJZTT8AUKI\/ueLXdflnUJxp9OBrusklLUSca1Wg23b0DRNrdjjX\/y54mq1ikKhcFm9Xi9YfDqdeHcLndg79Sv4iunDqVQKk8mEkyuNRgOlUomr5wnsuNvtIhqNYjabcQK0Wi0kk8mbG+hZAsWEJ5\/P52g2m4jFYm+REnfFBA1CJBKRE7nf7zl9nGKxKN\/1WffFdN2FQiH58Gq14vR17nZM0nA4jO12i8FgIDt\/lzxQXK\/XZae73Y4TYDQaIR6P43g8cvI8vmIaIMMwcDgcOLliWRbK5TJXj1GpVJBOp5FIJGCapsx+HK530G63eQf569brtRqxx\/l8lr+PUCYmaTabxXK5lLUSMd37+Xwem82GE0XiXC4Hx3GwWCwwHA4xHo9\/XzydTpHJZG4W3f9Kh+s7Qoj+FxqHkZPmFRufAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC\" width=\"30\" height=\"26\" alt=\"\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;= 0.5g<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The half-life of a radioactive element is 9days. Calculate the fraction that remains after 36days.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. 1\/32, B. 1\/16, C. &frac14;, D. 15\/32<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B (2009\/2010, no 14).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Given that the half-life of the radioactive element is 9days, it means that after every 9 days half of the original element is lost.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Lets take N<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sub>0<\/sub><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;as the original amount of the element and N represent current left over after each radiation<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">After the first 9 days &frac12; of N<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt;\"><sub>0<\/sub><\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;remains, N =&nbsp;<\/span><img src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAcAAAAaCAYAAAB7GkaWAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAC5SURBVChTvdK9DYQgGAZgaitLS+MYbkBPwxSs4ARuYGnlCCZQuIGFhdjYugKR9w5yxx0ak2u8N\/mSDx7+CgguYq1tfkdjzKs74DAMyLIsLAjYdR2UUiCEnPGdf2Lf92CMhZJSnnd+5050L7yoWx\/Uti2KokCe56CUxlhVlZ9wSdMU27adj933HUmS+D5CB5xzaK39OOCzgRAC8zx7cAlY17X\/Kuu6YhxHTNP0wbIso1qWJb7zGGtt8wArRnh53TXVUgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==\" width=\"7\" height=\"26\" al